IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: to rescue dogs from our local humane societies rehabilitate and train them to become service dogs to assist our local disabled veterans first responders and children with disabilities. The mission is to help the disabled lead more normal lives by having our service dogs help them 24 7.
IRS990.MissionDesc: To rescue dogs from our local humane societies train them to become working service dogs and place them with local disabled veterans first responders and autistic children to improve their lives. Our dogs are trained to mitigate both physical and psychological disabilities including PTSD and TBI. Our mission is to return to our clients some of the freedom they lost while defending that of all Americans and give disabled children a chance to become independent and acquire necessary social skills.
IRS990.Desc: Dasha was a 1 year old rescue when she was adopted and spent 6 months in intensive training as a PTSD anxiety and depression relief service dog. Dasha was placed with a scientific researcher employed by Clemson University who suffered from all of the above and was in jeopardy of losing her employment. 6 Months of training with the 37 year old woman and communication with the university to allow for ADA "reasonable accommodation" in the job and life is good again.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Louie. is a 1 year old Weimaraner who had a slightly botched surgery and due to a serious scar seemed unadoptable at the shelter. We adopted him and trained him for 1 year to be a mobility and stability service dog. We paired Louie with a 20 year career nurse who suffered a horrific fall lost her ability to work and had issues with walking balance and standing up. Louie is trained to keep her steady by bracing against her legs and assisting her in walking. He is a life changer for her.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Archie was hound mix rescued at 6 months of age - he was a stray most likely dumped by a hunter because he would not hunt. A year of training and Archie now serves a 7 year old boy with autism going to school with him and spending 24 7 keeping him safe. Archie has given this boy a new independence and a new life.
